<h3><a href="https://stmargarets.london/archive/2019/11/lbrut-living-wage.html?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=traffic%2Bfrom%20newsletter">Richmond commits to real living wage</a></h3>

<p><img src="https://stmargarets.london/assets/images/2019/lbrut-living-wage.jpg" width="150" align="right" style="border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 1px;" alt="" /></p>

<p>Richmond Council has this week been accredited as a Living Wage Employer.</p>

<p>The Living Wage commitment recognises that everyone working at Richmond Council receives a minimum hourly wage of &pound;10.75. This rate is significantly higher than the Government minimum for over 25s, which currently stands at &pound;8.21 per hour.</p>

